title: IU battles, then falls to No.7 Michigan State
text:
IU battles, then falls to No.7 Michigan State 
By Dean Pantazi Indiana University Hoosiers October 24, 2015 Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 11:27 PM EDT 
EAST LANSING, Mich. (21 Alive) - Indiana stayed with unbeaten Michigan State for three quarters Saturday, but the Spartans hit them with 24 straight points in the fourth quarter to pull away for a 52-26 win over the Hoosiers. 
Nate Sudfeld tossed three touchdown passes as IU trailed only 21-20 at the half and 28-26 after three. 
Then the Spartans lowered the boom. 
Connor Cook threw for 398 yards and four touchdowns for MSU, now 8-0. 
Indiana after its 4-0 start is now 4-4 and 0-4 in the Big Ten.
